The paper discusses the use of quantum annealers for solving SAT and MaxSAT problems, which are typically studied in the areas of theoretical computer science and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are likely categories. The paper also involves encoding techniques and optimization, which are relevant to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper discusses the use of quantum annealers, which are a type of computer architecture, and therefore cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also a possible category.
